  "bib_entries": {
    "553856": {
      "title": "Matrix Theory in a Constant C Field Background",
      "abstract": "D0-branes moving in a constant antisymmetric C field are found to be described by quantum mechanics of the supersymmetric matrix model with a similarity transformation. Sometimes this similarity transformation is singular or ill-defined and cannot be ignored. As an example, when there are nonvanishing C-ij components, we obtain the theory for Dp-branes which is effectively the noncommutative super Yang-Mills theory. We also briefly discuss the effects of other nonvanishing components such as C+ij and C-ijk. (C) 2000 Elsevier Science B.V. All rights reserved."
